
1. Master Data Tables
MARA: Stores general material data for all materials in the system.
MARC: Holds plant-specific material data, including MRP views.
MAKT: Contains material descriptions in different languages.
CRHD: Work center header data, which defines the work center.
CRCA: Work center capacity allocation details.
CRAT: Work center descriptions.
STKO: BOM header data for a material.
STPO: BOM item details for components in the BOM.
PLKO: Routing header data for a material.
PLPO: Routing operation details.
MAPL: Links task lists (routing) to materials.

2. Demand Management & Planning
PBIM: Stores independent requirements for a material.
PBED: Contains detailed data for independent requirements.
MDVM: MRP area data for materials.
MDKP: Header data for MRP documents created during planning.
MDTB: MRP table that stores planning results.
MDLV: Parameters for MRP areas.

3. Production Orders
AUFK: Order master data for all types of orders.
AFKO: Header data for production orders.
AFPO: Item-level data for production orders.
AFVC: Operation details within a production order.
AFVV: Values related to operations in an order (like quantities, times).
RESB: Reservation data for dependent requirements.
COHV: Used for mass processing of production orders.

4. Capacity Planning
KBED: Capacity requirements records for work centers.
KAKO: Capacity header segment data.
KAPE: Capacity planning data for work centers.
S024: Capacity planning statistics.

5. Shop Floor Control
AFRU: Stores confirmation data for production orders.
AFVC: Operation details (also used in shop floor control).
AFVV: Operation values like actual times and quantities.
CATSDB: Time sheet data if integrated with HR for labor confirmations.
